Male genitalia (
Fig. 3
). Uncus lobes rather wide, with V-shaped indentation. Gnathos small, rounded. Tegumen short, with almost parallel sides. Valva clearly tapering proximally, costa strong with large hump before rounded cucullus. Digitate process (
Fig. 4
) rather slender with almost parallel sides, apex blunt. Juxta lobes medially produced, rounded towards oblique, setose. Vinculum with a medial ridge, gradually produced into short, blunt saccus. Phallus (
Fig. 5
) almost straight, distal end chisel-shaped, without cornuti.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 6
). Apophyses slender, of almost equal length. Antrum funnel-shaped, ventral margin slightly anteriorly curved, dorsal wall spined before ventral margin; colliculum moderately narrow, twice as long as apophyses posteriores. Signum rather large and wide, an elongate dentate plate.
